Samples often contained at least a few mites with epibionts. Several suctorian ciliates (Ciliophora: Suctorea) are known epibionts on aquatic arthropods, including mites ( Dovgal and Peši´c 2007 , 2012 ,
Dovgal et al. 2008
), and our samples occasionally contained small numbers of mites covered in unidentified suctorians. Additionally, unidentified bacteria were surprisingly abundant on the integument surface, especially within depressions ( Fig. 22 B-D, 27C).
